Wow what a whacky thing to get mad about.  And the reasoning behind giving this to wizards and only wizards is hilarious.<P>Slurm, I have to disagree with you too.  This seems more like fixing a game bug to me than anything else.<P>And it really doesn't define a class in any way at all notable, it seems to me.  Being able to summon your pet really doesn't mean much at all except in regard to pathing problems, which are very real and are a problem with the game.<P>For instance, when I fight in City of Mist, I will clear my way from the entrance to the stables and then head back past the house of goos to the walkway right before you hit the water where the reavers building is. <P>Now, getting the pet simply to FOLLOW me is very difficult.  He will stand right next to me, on "follow," and literally sprint away from me to wherever he thinks is a swell place to be...like right into the face of a far-off mob.  This is bad enough getting to the stables, but trying to get past the goo house becomes really time-consuming.  I have to click follow as fast as I can, non-stop, to get through the courtyard in front of the goos, and once I get past them it gets even worse.  It literally becomes almost impossible to keep the pet by my side no matter how fast I click.  Sometimes I just have to put him on "guard here" literally to give my hand a rest.  Getting to where I finally want to be -- the bridge before the water -- is extremely time-consuming and frustrating, and all I am doing is a very slow walk.  When I finally get to where I want to go, I can't park my pet where I want to, either, because he will sometimes sprint off after a kill.  <P>None of this stuff is in any sense adding to roleplaying, or an intended part of the game, or helping to define my class for me.  It's simply buggy gameplay, and very, very tedious and frustrating.  It's really not a desireable thing or something that I think can be justified in terms of improving gameplay in any way.<P>And I don't think any mage in my group would feel badly if we could just all get our pets moving properly, or have an alternative if we couldn't.  If I could just zap my pet over, we'd all be on our way.  <P>Pathing is SO ridiculously terrible in some places.  There's no reason you should have to spend three to five minutes to get your pet to follow you for somewhere around 100 to 150 feet of pretty much open ground.<P>Since this won't be fixed in the game, the summon companion spell seems a reasonable way around basically buggy gameplay.<P>Limiting it to one class, I think, would be saying bugs are okay for some players.  To which I'd have to respond, why?  We all know this is a problem.  Why SHOULD anybody have to deal with it?  I honestly don't think there's a good answer.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
